news.title: Mysuru development body unallotted sites issue resurfaces again
news.para: After the disclosure, Muda took up a drive to verify records and confirmed that 9,508 sites were still 'unallotted.' Muda authorities had claimed in the 2019 budget that they had paid Rs 9.3 lakh to the sub registrar's office to obtain encumbrance certificates of these sites.

news.title: Karnataka government mulls extension of 10% discount on guidance value
news.para: First introduced in January, the rebate was initially in force until March 31, but buoyed by the positive response, the government extended the discount till July 23.

news.title: Navi Mumbai's Rs 10,588 crore 20-year draft development plan unveiled
news.para: ​The civic body has come out with a 20-year plan and proposes to spend Rs 10,588 crore on the development of various amenities such as gardens, roads, sporting arena, social and cultural facilities and upgradation of Cidco developed infrastructure.

news.title: CARE Ratings upgrades credit rating of Omaxe
news.para: Omaxe has repaid net Rs 550 crore to lenders as principal payment and reduced its debt from Rs 1400 crores to Rs 850 crore as on March 31, 2022.

news.title: Too much to ask developer to execute sale deed after 16 years, says SC
news.para: In its December 2019 verdict, the NCDRC had also directed the complainant to pay the balance sale consideration of Rs 6.49 lakh within four weeks to the developer.

news.title: Indiabulls Real Estate posts Rs 52 crore net loss in April-June 2022
news.para: Total income fell to Rs 164.18 crore in the April-June quarter from Rs 532.03 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: ED attaches Rs 300 crore assets of Bengaluru-based Mantri Developers
news.para: ​The federal agency said a provisional order for attachment has been issued under PMLA, 2002, against the company for "cheating" home buyers of 'Mantri Serenity', 'Mantri Web City' and 'MantriEnergia' residential projects.

news.title: SC seeks reply from states on deviations in RERA rules in their jurisdictions in three weeks
news.para: It said that both amicus and the ASG should prepare a model builder-buyer agreement based on the responses of the State governments leaving some degree of flexibility to make some deviations as per the local needs.

news.title: Dubai ruler becomes second-largest investor in Emaar Properties
news.para: Dubai's Emaar, the emirate's top developer, said in a statement it had reached a deal with Dubai Holding, Sheikh Mohammed bin Rashid Al Maktoum's investment vehicle, to buy its stake in their Dubai Creek Harbour joint venture.

news.title: The India Cements' net profit rises to 79.98 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: Its revenue from operations was up 44.87 per cent to Rs 1,514.35 crore in the first quarter of this fiscal. The same stood at Rs 1,045.25 crore a year ago.

news.title: Punjab Cabinet approves revision in sand rate, fixes MRP for gravel
news.para: ​The Cabinet also approved a new policy for crusher units and decided to impose an environment charge of Rs 1 per cubic feet on output material, which will fetch Rs 225 crore to the state exchequer.

news.title: Arvind SmartSpaces to set up Rs 900 crore housing platform with HDFC Capital
news.para: ​In a regulatory filing, Arvind SmartSpaces Ltd (ASL) informed that its Board has approved the creation of the Rs 900 crore residential development platform with HDFC Capital Advisors as investment manager of HDFC Capital Affordable Real Estate Fund- 3 (HCARE- 3).

news.title: Ahmedabad: Rs 22 crore cheating plaint filed against builders of Floris-41 project
news.para: Raju Patel, 43, a resident of Jodhpur, stated in his complaint that in 2016 he went to the office of Priti as he wanted to buy a flat in the Floris 41 scheme. At the office, Patel met Navin Thakkar, Haresh, Nagindas and Pradip Akhani.

news.title: Sebi extends time till Aug 31 to auction properties of Mega Mould, Remac Realty
news.para: The regulator will auction a total of four properties of these two firms for a reserve price totalling Rs 4.05 crore. The auction will be conducted online from 1030 hours to 1230 hours.

news.title: Realty market improves after Jaipur development body issues pattas to plot owners
news.para: Not only property rates have increased, but number of transactions and queries for plots has also witnessed a gradual increase.
